    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's complicated, but it feels like when people argue for the higher wage, they're mostly just focusing on how it helps employees without really looking at the math for the person running the shop. on the flip side, people against it often sound like they just don't care about workers at all. is there a way to look at this that isn't just picking a side based on whether you care more about a business's bottom line or a worker's paycheck?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
